{"lemma":"شَفْعُ","slug":"شَفْعُ","root":"ش.ف.ع","root_slug":"ش-ف-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ف-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَفْع","root":"شفع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n22638"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to double; to add to"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to intercede"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of شَفَعَ (šafaʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"double, pair","examples":[{"text":"وَٱلۡفَجۡرِ، وَلَیَالٍ عَشۡرࣲ، وَٱلشَّفۡعِ وَٱلۡوَتۡرِ، وَٱلَّیۡلِ إِذَا یَسۡرِ.","english":"By the dawn, And [by] ten nights, And [by] the even and the odd, And [by] the night when it passes."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ش ف ع (š f ʕ). Compare Hebrew שפע."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22638","headword_ar":"شَفْعٌ","root":"$fE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"witorN","text_ar":"وِتْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawojN","text_ar":"زَوْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawojN","text_ar":"زَوْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes, but rarely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple together;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes, (see for instance"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zakaA","text_ar":"زَكَا"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an even number, a number that may be divided into two equal numbers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, K:) also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one with which another is made to be a pair"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"couple:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [and, as will be seen in what follows,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one with which an odd number is made to be an even number:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ifaAEN","text_ar":"شِفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ofaAEN","text_ar":"اَشْفَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlS~alaApu bayona AlA^a$ofaAEi","text_ar":"الصَّلَاةُ بَيْنَ الاَشْفَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~araAwiyH","text_ar":"التَّرَاوِيح"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarowiyHapN","text_ar":"تَرْوِيحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~afoEu","text_ar":"الشَّفْعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The day of the sacrifice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K;) thus in the words of the Kur [lxxxix. 2]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l$~afoEi","text_ar":"وَا@لشَّفْعِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@lowitori","text_ar":"وَا@لْوِتْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwtr","text_ar":"الوتر"},{"kind":"text","text":"being meant the day of 'Arafát: (O:) or in this instance it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the creatures of God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,) because of the saying in the Kur [li. 49], “ and of everything we have created two of a pair; ” (K;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwtr","text_ar":"الوتر"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning God: (O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adam's wife;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwtr","text_ar":"الوتر"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning Adam, who was made a pair with her: (I'Ab, O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adam's children:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two days after the sacrifice;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwtr","text_ar":"الوتر"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the third day: (O, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwtr","text_ar":"الوتر"},{"kind":"text","text":", those who compose an odd number;] because of the saying in the Kur [lviii. 8], “ there can be no secret discourse of three, but He is the maker of them, with Himself, to be four: ” (K:) or the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~afoEu waAlwitoru","text_ar":"الشَّفْعُ وَالوِتْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prayers;"},{"kind":"text","text":"of which some are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoE","text_ar":"شَفْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. an even number of rek'ahs], and some are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"witor","text_ar":"وِتْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. an odd number of rek'ahs]: (O, TA:) [for] it is said that all the numbers consist of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$afoE","text_ar":"شَفْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"witor","text_ar":"وِتْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","TA"]}]}}